@NODE "ScrollWindowRaster" "intuition.library/ScrollWindowRaster()"
@{b}

   NAME@{ub}
        @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542} -- Intuition-friendly @{"ScrollRasterBF()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRasterBF"} (V39)@{b}

   SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}(win, dx, dy, xmin, ymin, xmax, ymax)
                           A1   D0  D1  D2    D3    D4    D5

        void @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}(@{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *, @{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54}, @{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54},
            @{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54}, @{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54}, @{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54}, @{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54});@{b}

   FUNCTION@{ub}
        Calls @{"graphics.library/ScrollRasterBF()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRasterBF"}, which moves
        the bits in the raster by (dx,dy) towards (0,0)
        The space vacated is filled by calling @{"EraseRect()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/EraseRect"}.
        NOTE: that vacated space is _not_ considered damage!
        The scroll operation is limited to the rectangle defined
        by (xmin,ymin)-(xmax,ymax). Bits outside will not be
        affected. If (xmax,ymax) is outside the rastport then use
        the lower right corner of the rastport.

        If a window is partly obscured, then it is possible for
        @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}() to scroll some of the obscured
        area into view.  If the window is simple-refresh, then
        the formerly obscured area is damage, and the application
        needs to repair it.  If Intuition detects damage as a result
        of @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}(), it will send an @{"IDCMP_REFRESHWINDOW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 834}
        event to the application's window.  This handling of damage
        is the principal reason @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}() is preferred
        to @{"ScrollRaster()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRaster"} and @{"ScrollRasterBF()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRasterBF"}.@{b}

   INPUTS@{ub}
        win - pointer to a Window structure
        dx,dy are integers that may be postive, zero, or negative
        xmin,ymin - upper left of bounding rectangle
        xmax,ymax - lower right of bounding rectangle@{b}

   NOTES@{ub}
        This call uses @{"ScrollRasterBF()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRasterBF"}, which calls @{"EraseRect()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/EraseRect"}
        when clearing the newly exposed area. This allows use of
        a custom layer backfill hook.

        IMPORTANT:  boopsi gadgets should use @{"ScrollRaster()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRaster"} or
        @{"ScrollRasterBF()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRasterBF"} directly!  Never call @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}()
        from inside a boopsi gadget's method handler.  Note that
        Intuition will detect and handle damage caused by such use
        of @{"ScrollRaster()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRaster"} or @{"ScrollRasterBF()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRasterBF"}, for gadgets with
        the @{"GMORE_SCROLLRASTER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 505} property.

        VERY IMPORTANT:  if you have any gadgets in your simple-refresh
        window with the @{"GMORE_SCROLLRASTER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 505} property, you must use
        @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}() instead of @{"ScrollRaster()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRaster"} or @{"ScrollRasterBF()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRasterBF"}.
        Handling of gadget scroll damage is incompatible with continued
        use of these graphics functions in an Intuition window.
        NB:  If you're using a gadget class whose source code you do
        not control, that class might be using @{"GMORE_SCROLLRASTER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 505} or
        might start to in a future version.  For that reason, you
        should use @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}() if you are using any such gadgets.@{b}

   BUGS@{ub}
        In intuition.library V39 and V40 @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}() must
        be considered unsafe in connection with gadget event handling
        and windows which do not have the @{"WA_NoCareRefresh" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1300} attribute set.
        A race condition may occur which will cause write accesses
        to unallocated memory and keep the @{"IDCMP_REFRESHWINDOW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 834} message
        from getting delivered.

        The recommended workaround for this problem is to use
        @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}() only in @{"SMART_REFRESH" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/iobsolete.h/File" 147} windows which have
        the @{"WA_NoCareRefresh" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1300} attribute set. Of course, which such
        windows there will be no difference in functionality between
        @{"ScrollWindowRaster" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 542}() and @{"ScrollRasterBF()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRasterBF"}.@{b}

   SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"graphics.library/ScrollRaster()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRaster"}, @{"graphics.library/ScrollRasterBF()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/ScrollRasterBF"}
        @{"graphics.library/EraseRect()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/EraseRect"}, @{"WA_BackFill" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1284}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SetAttrsA" "intuition.library/SetAttrsA()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"SetAttrsA" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 468} -- Specify attribute values for an object. (V36)
        @{"SetAttrs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 473} -- Varargs stub for @{"SetAttrsA" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 468}(). (V36)@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        result = @{"SetAttrsA" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 468}( Object, TagList )
        D0                  A0      A1

        @{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52} @{"SetAttrsA" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 468}( @{"APTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 49}, @{"struct TagItem" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/utility/tagitem.h/File" 32} * );

        result = @{"SetAttrs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 473}( Object, Tag1, ... )

        @{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52} @{"SetAttrs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 473}( @{"APTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 49}, @{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52}, ... );@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Specifies a set of attribute/value pairs with meaning as
        defined by a 'boopsi' object's class.

        This function does not provide enough context information or
        arbitration for boopsi gadgets which are attached to windows
        or requesters.  For those objects, use @{"SetGadgetAttrs()" LINK "SetGadgetAttrsA"}.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
        Object = abstract pointer to a boopsi object.
        TagList = array of TagItem structures with attribute/value pairs.@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        The object does whatever it wants with the attributes you provide.
        The return value tends to be non-zero if the changes would require
        refreshing gadget imagery, if the object is a gadget.@{b}

    NOTES@{ub}
        This function invokes the @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65} method with a @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101} GadgetInfo
        parameter.@{b}

    BUGS@{ub}@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"NewObject()" LINK "NewObject"}, @{"DisposeObject()" LINK "DisposeObject"}, @{"GetAttr()" LINK "GetAttr"}, @{"MakeClass()" LINK "MakeClass"},
        Document "Basic @{"Object" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 19}-Oriented Programming @{"System" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/dos/SystemTagList"} for @{"Intuition" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 33}"
        and the "boopsi @{"Class" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classes.h/File" 36} Reference" document.

