@NODE "SetDMRequest" "intuition.library/SetDMRequest()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"SetDMRequest" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 183} -- Set the DMRequest of a window.@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        success = @{"SetDMRequest" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 183}( Window, DMRequest )
        D0                      A0      A1

        @{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91} @{"SetDMRequest" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 183}( @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *, @{"struct Requester" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 144} * );@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Attempts to set the DMRequest into the specified window.
        The DMRequest is the special requester that you attach to
        the double-click of the menu button which the user can then
        bring up on demand.  This routine WILL @{"NOT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1500} change the DMRequest
        if it's already set and is currently active (in use by the user).
        After having called @{"SetDMRequest" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 183}(), if you want to change the
        DMRequest, the correct way to start is by calling @{"ClearDMRequest()" LINK "ClearDMRequest"}
        until it returns a value of @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}; then you can call @{"SetDMRequest" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 183}()
        with the new DMRequest.

        If the @{"POINTREL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 179} flag is set in the DMRequest, the DMR will open as
        close to the pointer as possible.  The RelLeft/Top fields are
        for fine-tuning the position.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
        Window = pointer to the window from which the DMRequest is to be set
        DMRequest = a pointer to a requester@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        If the current DMRequest was not in use, sets the DMRequest
            pointer into the window and returns @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}.
        If the DMRequest was currently in use, doesn't change the pointer
            and returns @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}@{b}

    BUGS@{ub}@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"ClearDMRequest()" LINK "ClearDMRequest"}, @{"Request()" LINK "Request"}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SetEditHook" "intuition.library/SetEditHook()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"SetEditHook" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 335} -- Set global processing for string gadgets. (V36)@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        OldHook = @{"SetEditHook" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 335}( Hook )
        D0                     A0

        @{"struct Hook" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/utility/hooks.h/File" 28} *@{"SetEditHook" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 335}( @{"struct Hook" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/utility/hooks.h/File" 28} * );@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Sets new global editing hook for string gadgets.

        WARNING: The use and integration of this function has not
        been explored, and thus should be considered a risky function.
        Do *@{"NOT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1500}* use this in a commercial product until further notice.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
        Hook -- A pointer to a @{"struct Hook" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/utility/hooks.h/File" 28} which determines a function
          in your code to be called every time the user types a key.
          This is done before control is passed to the gadget custom
          editing hook, so affects ALL string gadgets.@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        Returns previous global edit hook structure.  You may need this
        hook if you wish to invoke the previous edit hook's behavior
        in addition to your own.@{b}

    NOTES@{ub}
        There are a few key differences between a global edit hook and the
        more famililar per-gadget StringExtend->EditHook field.  In the
        case of the latter, the hook's creator supplies a WorkBuffer.
        Intuition's idea of the result of a keystroke is stored in
        the SGWork structure (which references the WorkBuffer).  The
        state of the gadget before Intuition's hook acted is available in
        the StringInfo->Buffer, ->BufferPos, and ->NumChars fields.

        In the case of a global editing hook, your hook _becomes_
        Intuition's hook, which affects all gadgets, most of which
        do not have a WorkBuffer.  This means that if you invoke
        Intuition's original hook (which you got as the result of this
        function), there isn't any easy way for you to "undo" that after
        the fact.  This means that if Intuition's behavior for certain
        keystrokes is incompatible with your hook's objectives, then
        you must avoid calling Intuition's hook for those keys.  One
        approach is to run through your hook's code first, acting on
        those keys you wish to recognize.  Then, call Intuition's
        hook for those keys you do not recognize, or for those keys
        whose default actions you wish to add to.

        Do not forget to set @{"SGA_REDISPLAY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/sghooks.h/File" 116} when needed (see sghooks.h),
        and please be sure to give the SGWork->EditOp field a value
        which is as meaningful as possible.

        Currently, only @{"SGH_KEY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/sghooks.h/File" 124} messages are sent to the global edit
        hook, though custom edit hooks do receive @{"SGH_CLICK" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/sghooks.h/File" 125} messages
        in addition.

        Finally, there is currently no arbitration between a global
        edit hook and a custom edit hook as to ownership of keystrokes.
        It would be fair to expect that a custom edit hook would be
        written to match the current Intuition edit hook.  If your
        global edit hook acts on (say) up and down arrow keystrokes,
        an undesirable result may occur if some string gadget's custom
        hook also acts on these keystrokes.  There is currently
        no easy way to resolve this issue.@{b}

    BUGS@{ub}@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SetGadgetAttrsA" "intuition.library/SetGadgetAttrsA()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"SetGadgetAttrsA" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 481} -- Specify attribute values for a boopsi gadget. (V36)
        @{"SetGadgetAttrs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 486} -- Varargs stub for @{"SetGadgetAttrsA" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 481}(). (V36)@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        result = @{"SetGadgetAttrsA" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 481}( Gadget, Window, Requester, TagList )
        D0                        A0      A1      A2         A3

        @{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52} @{"SetGadgetAttrsA" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 481}( @{"struct Gadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 214} *, @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *,
                @{"struct Requester" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 144} *, @{"struct TagItem" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/utility/tagitem.h/File" 32} * );

        result = @{"SetGadgetAttrs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 486}( Gadget, Window, Requester, Tag1, ...)

        @{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52} @{"SetGadgetAttrs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 486}( @{"struct Gadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 214} *, @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *,
                @{"struct Requester" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 144} *, @{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52}, ... );@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Same as @{"SetAttrs()" LINK "SetAttrsA"}, but provides context information and
        arbitration for classes which implement custom Intuition gadgets.

        You should use this function for boopsi gadget objects which have
        already been added to a requester or a window, or for "models" which
        propagate information to gadget already added.

        Typically, the gadgets will refresh their visuals to reflect
        changes to visible attributes, such as the value of a slider,
        the text in a string-type gadget, the selected state of a button.

        You can use this as a replacement for @{"SetAttrs()" LINK "SetAttrsA"}, too, if you
        specify @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101} for the 'Window' and 'Requester' parameters.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
        Gadget = abstract pointer to a boopsi gadget
        Window = window gadget has been added to using @{"AddGList()" LINK "AddGList"} or @{"AddGadget()" LINK "AddGadget"}
        Requester = for REQGADGETs, requester containing the gadget
        TagList = array of TagItem structures with attribute/value pairs.@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        The object does whatever it wants with the attributes you provide,
        which might include updating its gadget visuals.

        The return value tends to be non-zero if the changes would require
        refreshing gadget imagery, if the object is a gadget.@{b}

    NOTES@{ub}
        This function invokes the @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65} method with a GadgetInfo
        derived from the 'Window' and 'Requester' pointers.@{b}

    BUGS@{ub}
        Prior to V39, this function ran with inadequate locking against
        the calls that Intuition's input task makes to the gadgets.
        To run properly prior to V39, this function, input processing,
        and and the gadget's dispatcher must be mutually re-entrant.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"NewObject()" LINK "NewObject"}, @{"DisposeObject()" LINK "DisposeObject"}, @{"GetAttr()" LINK "GetAttr"}, @{"MakeClass()" LINK "MakeClass"},
        Document "Basic @{"Object" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 19}-Oriented Programming @{"System" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/dos/SystemTagList"} for @{"Intuition" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 33}"
        and the "boopsi @{"Class" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classes.h/File" 36} Reference" document.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SetMenuStrip" "intuition.library/SetMenuStrip()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"SetMenuStrip" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 187} -- Attach a menu strip to a window.@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        Success = @{"SetMenuStrip" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 187}( Window, Menu )
        D0                      A0      A1

        @{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91} @{"SetMenuStrip" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 187}( @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *, @{"struct Menu" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 60} * );@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Attaches the menu strip to the window.  After calling this routine,
        if the user presses the menu button, this specified menu strip
        will be displayed and accessible by the user.

        Menus with zero menu items are not allowed.

        NOTE:  You should always design your menu strip changes to be a
        two-way operation, where for every menu strip you add to your
        window you should always plan to clear that strip sometime.  Even
        in the simplest case, where you will have just one menu strip for
        the lifetime of your window, you should always clear the menu strip
        before closing the window.  If you already have a menu strip attached
        to this window, the correct procedure for changing to a new menu
        strip involves calling @{"ClearMenuStrip()" LINK "ClearMenuStrip"} to clear the old first.

        The sequence of events should be:
        - @{"OpenWindow()" LINK "OpenWindow"}
        - zero or more iterations of:
        - @{"SetMenuStrip" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 187}()
        - @{"ClearMenuStrip()" LINK "ClearMenuStrip"}
        - @{"CloseWindow()" LINK "CloseWindow"}@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
        Window = pointer to a Window structure
        Menu = pointer to the first menu in the menu strip@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95} if there were no problems.  @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95} always, since this routine
        will wait until it is OK to proceed.@{b}

    BUGS@{ub}@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"ClearMenuStrip()" LINK "ClearMenuStrip"}, @{"ResetMenuStrip()" LINK "ResetMenuStrip"}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SetMouseQueue" "intuition.library/SetMouseQueue()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"SetMouseQueue" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 339} -- Change limit on pending mouse messages. (V36)@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        oldQueueLength = @{"SetMouseQueue" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 339}( Window, QueueLength )
        D0                              A0      D0

        @{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51} @{"SetMouseQueue" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 339}( @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *, @{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55} );@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Changes the number of mouse messages that Intuition will allow
        to be outstanding for your window.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
        Window = your window
        QueueLength = the new value of outstanding mouse movement messages
          you wish to allow.@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        -1 if 'Window' is not known
        Otherwise the previous value of the queue limit.
        The corresponding function for changing the repeat key
        queue limit is not yet implemented.@{b}

    BUGS@{ub}@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"OpenWindow()" LINK "OpenWindow"}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SetPointer" "intuition.library/SetPointer()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"SetPointer" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 191} -- Specify a pointer sprite image for a window.@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        @{"SetPointer" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 191}( Window, Pointer, Height, Width, XOffset, YOffset )
                    A0      A1       D0      D1     D2       D3

        @{"VOID" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 24} @{"SetPointer" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 191}( @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *, @{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55} *, @{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54}, @{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54}, @{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54}, @{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54} );@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Sets up the window with the sprite definition for the pointer.
        Then, whenever the window is the active one, the pointer
        image will change to the window's version.  If the window is
        the active one when this routine is called, the change takes
        place immediately.

        The XOffset and YOffset parameters are used to offset the
        upper-left corner of the hardware sprite image from what Intuition
        regards as the current position of the pointer.  Another way of
        describing it is as the offset from the "hot spot" of the pointer
        to the top-left corner of the sprite.  For instance, if you specify
        offsets of zero, zero, then the top-left corner of your sprite
        image will be placed at the mouse position.  On the other hand,
        if you specify an XOffset of -7 (remember, sprites are 16 pixels
        wide) then your sprite will be centered over the mouse position.
        If you specify an XOffset of -15, the right-edge of the sprite
        will be over the mouse position.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
        Window = pointer to the window to receive this pointer definition
        Pointer = pointer to the data definition of a sprite
        Height = the height of the pointer
        Width = the width of the sprite (must be less than or equal to sixteen)
        XOffset = the offset for your sprite from the mouse position
        YOffset = the offset for your sprite from the mouse position@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        None@{b}

    BUGS@{ub}@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"SetWindowPointerA()" LINK "SetWindowPointerA"}, @{"ClearPointer()" LINK "ClearPointer"}, ROM Kernel Manual: Libraries

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SetPrefs" "intuition.library/SetPrefs()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"SetPrefs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 227} -- Set Intuition preferences data.@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        Prefs = @{"SetPrefs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 227}( PrefBuffer, Size, Inform )
        D0                A0          D0    D1

        @{"struct Preferences" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/preferences.h/File" 58} *@{"SetPrefs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 227}( @{"struct Preferences" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/preferences.h/File" 58} *, @{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51}, @{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91} );@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Sets new preferences values.  Copies the first 'Size' bytes
        from your preferences buffer to the system preferences table,
        and puts them into effect.

        The 'Inform' parameter, if @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}, indicates that an @{"IDCMP_NEWPREFS" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 846}
        message is to be sent to all windows that have the @{"IDCMP_NEWPREFS" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 846}
        IDCMPFlag set.

        It is legal to set a partial copy of the Preferences structure.
        The most frequently changed values are grouped at the beginning
        of the Preferences structure.

        New for V36:  A new and more extensible method for supplying
        Preferences has been introduced in V36, and relies on file
        system notification.  The Intuition preferences items rely
        also on the IPrefs program.  Certain elements of the
        Preferences structure have been superseded by this new method.
        (Elements are generally superseded as new hardware or software
        features demand more information than fits in @{"struct Preferences" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/preferences.h/File" 58}.
        Parts of @{"struct Preferences" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/preferences.h/File" 58} must be ignored so that applications
        calling @{"GetPrefs()" LINK "GetPrefs"}, modifying some other part of @{"struct Preferences" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/preferences.h/File" 58},
        then calling @{"SetPrefs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 227}(), don't end up truncating the extended
        data).

        Pointer Preferences:  Starting with V36, pointer changes
        submitted through @{"SetPrefs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 227}() are only heeded until the first
        time IPrefs informs Intuition of a V36-style pointer preferences
        file.  In V39 and higher, only the pointer from the initial
        @{"SetPrefs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 227}() (i.e. devs:system-configuration) is heeded.

        Palette Preferences:  Starting with V39, color changes submitted
        through @{"SetPrefs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 227}() are ignored after the first time IPrefs sends
        Intuition new style palette preferences.

        FontHeight and LaceWB:  These are only respected from
        devs:system-configuration.

        View centering and size:  Changes to ViewX/YOffset and
        Row/ColumnSizeChange only apply to the default monitor
        (@{"NTSC" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/graphics/gfxbase.h/File" 138} or @{"PAL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/graphics/gfxbase.h/File" 140}), and not to other monitors such as Productivity.

        Other fields may be superseded in the future.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
        PrefBuffer = pointer to the memory buffer which contains your
            desired settings for Intuition preferences
        Size = the number of bytes in your PrefBuffer, the number of bytes
           you want copied to the system's internal preference settings
        Inform = whether you want the information of a new preferences
            setting propagated to all windows.@{b}

    NOTES@{ub}
        Unless you are responding to a user's explicit request to
        change Preferences (for example, you are writing a Preferences
        editor), you should probably avoid using this function.
        The user's Preferences should be respected, not overridden.@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        Returns your parameter PrefBuffer.@{b}

    BUGS@{ub}@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"GetDefPrefs()" LINK "GetDefPrefs"}, @{"GetPrefs()" LINK "GetPrefs"}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SetPubScreenModes" "intuition.library/SetPubScreenModes()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"SetPubScreenModes" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 371} -- Establish global public screen behavior. (V36)@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        OldModes = @{"SetPubScreenModes" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 371}( Modes )
        D0                            D0

        @{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55} @{"SetPubScreenModes" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 371}( @{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55} );@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Sets @{"GLOBAL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 17} Intuition public screen modes.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
